#: ../../source/tmp.rst:2
msgid "OpenModelica 1.3.1, November 2005"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:4
msgid "This release has several important highlights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:6
msgid ""
"This is also the \\*first\\* release for which the New BSD (Berkeley) "
"open-source license applies to the source code, including the whole "
"compiler and run-time system. This makes is possible to use OpenModelica "
"for both academic and commercial purposes without restrictions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:12
msgid "OpenModelica Compiler (OMC)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:14
msgid ""
"This release includes a significantly improved OpenModelica Compiler "
"(OMC):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:17
msgid "Support for hybrid and discrete-event simulation (if-equations,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:18
msgid ""
"if-expressions, when-equations; not yet if-statements and when-"
"statements). - Parsing of full Modelica 2.2 - Improved support for "
"external functions. - Vectorization of function arguments; each-"
"modifiers, better implementation of replaceable, better handling of "
"structural parameters, better support for vector and array operations, "
"and many other improvements. - Flattening of the Modelica Block library "
"version 1.5 (except a few models), and simulation of most of these. - "
"Automatic index reduction (present also in previous release). - Updated "
"User's Guide including examples of hybrid simulation and external "
"functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:30
msgid "OpenModelica Shell (OMShell)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:32
msgid ""
"An improved window-based interactive command shell, now including command"
" completion and better editing and font size support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:36
msgid "OpenModelica Notebook (OMNotebook)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:38
msgid ""
"A free implementation of an OpenModelica notebook (OMNotebook), for "
"electronic books with course material, including the DrModelica "
"interactive course material. It is possible to simulate and plot from "
"this notebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:44
msgid "OpenModelica Eclipse Plug-in (MDT)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:46
msgid ""
"An early alpha version of the first Eclipse plug-in (called MDT for "
"Modelica Development Tooling) for Modelica Development. This version "
"gives compilation support and partial support for browsing Modelica "
"package hierarchies and classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:52
msgid "OpenModelica Development Environment (OMDev)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:54
msgid ""
"The following mechanisms have been put in place to support OpenModelica "
"development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:57
msgid "Bugzilla support for OpenModelica bug tracking, accessible to anybody."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:58
msgid "A system for automatic regression testing of the compiler and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tmp.rst:59
msgid ""
"simulator, (+ other system parts) usually run at check in time. - Version"
" handling is done using SVN, which is better than the previously used CVS"
" system. For example, name change of modules is now possible within the "
"version handling system."
msgstr ""

